<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>for all the world • for the world</xh5><p> <i>for all the world—</i>1. is used to emphasize assertions of likeness: She looked <u>for all the world</u> like her twin sister. 2. without the slightest doubt: I thought <u>for all the world</u> that the car would plunge headlong down the bank. 3. <i>(emphatic, negat.)</i> on no account; not for the greatest possible reward: I am sure I would not do such a thing <u>for all the world</u>.</p><p> <i>for the world</i>— = for all the world 3: I wouldn’t <u>for the world</u> go into that deserted house at this time of night.</p> </entry>
